<h1>Problem 2217 - 2023 ELMOSL, N2, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Determine the greatest positive integer \(n\) for which there exists a sequence of distinct positive integers \(s_1\), \(s_2\), \(\ldots\), \(s_n\) satisfying\[s_1^{s_2}=s_2^{s_3}=\cdots=s_{n-1}^{s_n}.\]</p>
